==English==

===Etymology===
From Old (and modern) French ''[[coffre]]'', from Latin ''[[cophinus]]'', from Greek [[κόφινος]] ‘basket’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈkɒfə/}}
* Homophones: [[cougher]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# a [[strongbox]]: a strong [[chest]] or [[box]] used for keeping [[money]] or [[valuables]] safe.
#{{architecture}} an ornamental sunken panel in a ceiling or dome.
# a [[cofferdam]]
# a supply or store of money, often belonging to an organization

===Transitive verb===
{{en-verb}}

# to put money or valuables in a coffer
# to decorate something, especially a ceiling, with [[coffers]]

